The paper proposes a measure for quantifying the impact of research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on manuscripts and researchers suggests that the paper may belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. The measure proposed may also be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with evaluating the impact of research. Additionally, the measure may be applicable to Cryptography (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, as these fields also involve evaluating the impact of research on a larger scale.
